hint.text: Represent the given number as a product of its prime factors

solution.text:
\(_{{(j**m)*(k**n)*(l**o)}}_\)
\(=_{{str(j) + ('\\times' + str(j))*(m-1)}}_ \times _{{str(k) + ('\\times' + str(k))*(n-1)}}_ _{{'\\times' + str(l) + ('\\times' + str(l))*(o-1) if (o>0) else ''}}_\)
\(\)
\(\)
Therefore, cube root of \(_{{(j**m)*(k**n)*(l**o)}}_\)
\(=\sqrt[3]{_{{(j**m)*(k**n)*(l**o)}}_}=\sqrt[3]{_{{str(j) + ('\\times' + str(j))*(m-1)}}_ \times _{{str(k) + ('\\times' + str(k))*(n-1)}}_ _{{'\\times' + str(l) + ('\\times' + str(l))*(o-1) if (o>0) else ''}}_}\)
\(=\sqrt[3]{_{j}_^_{m}_ \times _{k}_^_{n}_ _{{'\\times' + str(l) + '^' + str(o) if (o>0) else ''}}_}=_{j}_ \times _{k}_ _{{'\\times' + str(l) if (o>0) else ''}}_\)
\(=_{{(j*k*l) if (o>0) else (j*k)}}_\)

content.text: What is the cube root of \(_{{(j**m)*(k**n)*(l**o)}}_\)?
